Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.22,0:00:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The initial bet is 8 Million.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.54,0:00:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,8 MILLION!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.94,0:00:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't accept it, I'm out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.54,0:00:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I GET IT\NI'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.54,0:00:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you isn't it?\NYou're my opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.45,0:00:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The more {\b1}insane{\b0} it is, the more interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.48,0:00:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That guy. He wants something.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.68,0:00:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How about just a normal person for once?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.45,0:01:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We have something to discuss with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.91,0:01:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.08,0:01:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Just wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.97,0:01:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,AKAGI!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.37,0:01:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Cutting it a bit close, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.60,0:01:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,S-sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.85,0:01:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.42,0:01:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.42,0:01:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ippatsu, Honitsu, 2 Dora. Dealer points 4,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.65,0:01:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, your victory,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.60,0:01:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Is far off.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.02,0:01:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You're an interesting man.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.91,0:01:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That mask of yours. I'm going to tear it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.25,0:02:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,With that last dealer bonus,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.71,0:02:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes to 16,000 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.42,0:02:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.11,0:02:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, to be long winded about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.11,0:02:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,this match between you and Ichikawa
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.85,0:02:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is a death-match which will continue indefinitely until someone runs out of points.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.83,0:02:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do anything rash.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.83,0:02:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.62,0:02:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,without making a direct hit on Ichikawa,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.91,0:02:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no way to win this match.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.22,0:02:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.00,0:02:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a long way off yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.37,0:02:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Just accumulate some points first.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.80,0:02:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,16,000 points isn't that bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.11,0:02:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll start with taking what's easy to take.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.14,0:02:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,"Taking what's easy to take?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.02,0:03:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry for keeping you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.82,0:03:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, shall we begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.11,0:03:22.28,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(155.493,142)}South Hand Four
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.11,0:03:22.28,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(586.479,360)}1st Honba
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.02,0:03:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,4 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.02,0:03:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,3 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.20,0:03:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,3 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.05,0:03:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,9 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.20,0:03:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,HHmmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.20,0:03:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The players to the left and right,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.68,0:04:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They're discarding tiles of no use to Akagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.91,0:04:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They're only playing to fill the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.82,0:04:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Their only concern is to remain inconspicuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.82,0:04:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They avoid this sink-or-swim contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.97,0:04:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They do all they can to avoid dealing into anyone's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.77,0:04:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They're playing to stay out of the conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.77,0:04:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,1 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.77,0:04:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And Akagi is all too well aware of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.31,0:04:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,East.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.28,0:04:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi on 7 Pin discard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.29,0:04:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.29,0:04:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He hints at having a Tanpin hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.65,0:04:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but truly has a "hell" wait for a single tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.62,0:04:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,4 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.40,0:05:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They can only think of not dealing into a hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.11,0:05:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,so from there, they'll step into the trap themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.74,0:05:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,West.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.74,0:05:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.74,0:05:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi, Ippatsu, Ipeikou.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.91,0:05:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,One dora. Dealer bonus. 1,200/1,300 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.57,0:05:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.51,0:05:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"Taking what's easy to take."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.20,0:05:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.20,0:05:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,With that, 28,300 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.45,0:05:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this kid not have the stomach to target Ichikawa himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.20,0:05:58.40,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(148.732,154)}South Hand Four
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.20,0:05:58.40,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(571.267,366)}2nd Honba
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.50,0:05:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Needless to say, Akagi was still close to death...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.68,0:05:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,7 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.82,0:06:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Chii.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.82,0:06:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,7-8-9 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.25,0:06:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,4 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.15,0:06:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,When Akagi, made this call,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.97,0:06:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the players to the left and right
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.97,0:06:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,began to avoid Man tile discards.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.68,0:06:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,2 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.31,0:06:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,5 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.57,0:06:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,5 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.57,0:06:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,2 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.71,0:06:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,7 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.20,0:06:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,3 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.20,0:06:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was already too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.20,0:06:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,On Akagi's next turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.20,0:06:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the 9th turn of the others avoiding Man tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.88,0:06:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,4 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.22,0:06:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.42,0:06:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,With that Pon, the chances of  his having a Honiitsu or Chanta hand have vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.99,0:06:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What on earth is this kid thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.37,0:06:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,9 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.31,0:07:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,West wind Kan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.05,0:07:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,4 Dora!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.20,0:07:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,6 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.42,0:07:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He probably doesn't have a Yakuman hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.69,0:07:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So. Is he aiming for a hidden triplet of honor tiles?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.48,0:07:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.48,0:07:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows there's only two tiles left between east, south, red and green dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.68,0:07:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All that remains is White Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.82,0:07:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A concealed white dragon triplet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.82,0:07:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore he's got a naked single tile wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.62,0:07:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as far as that's concerned,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.62,0:07:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The others cannot discard the 4th White Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.54,0:07:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Dealing into someone's hand that has called 3 times in one game is the lowest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.13,0:08:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,White Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.22,0:08:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,White dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.25,0:08:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus, he can't be waiting for a white dragon triplet!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.92,0:08:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and so therefore...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.42,0:08:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All that remains is a double pair wait on honors.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.51,0:08:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No one's going to discard those either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.87,0:08:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,8 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.28,0:08:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.28,0:08:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what in living fuck does he think he's doing!?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.68,0:08:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,4 Pin Kan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.94,0:09:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,1 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.63,0:09:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,3 Kan with 4 Dora?!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.57,0:09:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,NARUHODO
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.65,0:09:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,At any time he can get up to a Haneman hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.48,0:09:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he aim for this from the start?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.74,0:09:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,6 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.60,0:09:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A safe tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.57,0:09:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,9 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.68,0:09:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,As expected. They're only discarding safe tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.20,0:09:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,6 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.94,0:10:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,5 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.05,0:10:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Safe tiles are all well and good, but what happens when they run out?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.06,0:10:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.06,0:10:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What is he waiting on?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.54,0:10:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That time when he drew his Rinshan replacement tile...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.05,0:10:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Discarding that 1 Sou,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.45,0:10:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The one tile remaining in his hand must be something we haven't thought of.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.05,0:10:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That time, the 1 Sou was a "live" previously undiscarded tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.94,0:10:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The best kind of tile for a Tsumo self-drawn win.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.08,0:10:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus if he discarded the 1 Sou,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.54,0:10:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he aiming for a Ron direct hit win?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.54,0:10:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he waiting on a tile they already have?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.11,0:10:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And if he's doing that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.11,0:10:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They won't discard either Man or Honor tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.97,0:11:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but rather Pin or Sou tiles instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.04,0:11:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Think carefully, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.04,0:11:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.77,0:11:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you agonize,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.77,0:11:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the more you play into my plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.05,0:11:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,3 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.02,0:11:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.02,0:11:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,3 Kans, 4 Dora.\N18,000/18,600 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.54,0:11:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You done did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.82,0:11:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well played my good sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.42,0:11:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.42,0:11:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Master, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.38,0:11:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Break time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.51,0:11:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How many including that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.19,0:11:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,18,000 points plus dealer bonus.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.20,0:11:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Makes 46,900 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.68,0:12:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.72,0:12:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoiding Ichikawa at the start,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.22,0:12:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to snap up the small fry, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.22,0:12:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say that was it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.11,0:12:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, were you aiming for that 3 Pin single tile wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.17,0:12:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.15,0:12:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,My goal was Sou or Pin accumulated tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.25,0:12:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,"Accumulated tiles?"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.25,0:12:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I discarded this 1 Sou,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.25,0:12:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the others read it as my aiming for a Ron direct hit win.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.33,0:12:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,1 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.73,0:12:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly at that time the 1 Sou was a Shonpai "live" tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.20,0:12:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.00,0:12:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you discarded a tile that could give you a Tsumo sefl-drawn win,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.25,0:12:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it means you're aiming for a Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.01,0:12:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This Chi I called out on the 2nd turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.88,0:12:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,caused them to avoid discarding Man tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.88,0:12:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,2 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.19,0:12:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,5 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.19,0:12:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,7 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.19,0:13:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,5 Pin.\N2 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.82,0:13:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,3 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.82,0:13:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That is to say, in their hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.31,0:13:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,mostly Man or Honor tiles remained.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.22,0:13:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus those Man and Honor tiles were difficult to get rid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.67,0:13:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What Sou or Pin tiles which remained in their hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.54,0:13:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,fewer and fewer remained that could avoid a single tile wait direct hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.20,0:13:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,At such a time, their strategy would be...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.11,0:13:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to discard from a pair or triplet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.17,0:13:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, if they survive one discard,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.00,0:13:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll have two or three safe turns.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.11,0:13:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.74,0:13:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what tiles have they accumulated?
