Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.88,0:26:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,or will Akagi make a comeback?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.55,0:26:50.82,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(221.409,154)}East Hand Two (repeated)
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.50,0:26:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,White dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.64,0:27:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,4 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.36,0:27:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,5 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.65,0:27:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,North.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.38,0:27:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.88,0:27:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not Zetsu Ichi mon anymore; it's Zetsu {\b1\i1}Ni{\b0\i0} Mon, eliminating {\b1\i1}two{\b0\i0} suits.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.50,0:27:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This just gets better and better.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.80,0:27:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This is  a little reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.60,0:27:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In taking charge of the game flow,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.88,0:27:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa has the advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.42,0:28:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,A closed wait in tenpai with a hidden triple dora!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.24,0:28:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He's waiting on a 3, 6, or 9 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.56,0:28:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like the winner might be Ichikawa, as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.26,0:28:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,East Kan.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.84,0:28:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The new dora is 7 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.74,0:28:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi with 7 Man discard.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.34,0:28:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Riichi, hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.04,0:28:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I dare say Ichikawa is also in Tenpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.52,0:28:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And comparing that to Akagi...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.74,0:28:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He maybe one tile from a ChiiToitsu pairs only hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.90,0:28:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but at the same time the 9 Man he must discard is extremely dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.24,0:28:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Chii. 7-8-9.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.00,0:28:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,West.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.57,0:28:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Typical Akagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.38,0:29:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, he's not likely to have to discard the remaining 6 or 9 Man tiles, which are dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.92,0:29:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi means to use the 3, 6, and 9 Man in his hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.72,0:29:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore it's unlikely he'll discard them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.86,0:29:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,4 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.22,0:29:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Chii on 4 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.76,0:29:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,From a 3, 6, 9 Man wait,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.94,0:29:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,he changes to a 2, 5, or 8 Man wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.15,0:29:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The 8 Man is a tile Akagi seems likely to discard next.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.19,0:29:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But Akagi isn't beaten yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.86,0:29:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,7 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.39,0:29:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi.\N6-7-8 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.54,0:29:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Using the 8 Man,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.92,0:29:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He's sidestepped Ichikawa's waits once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.08,0:29:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,8 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.44,0:30:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,2 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.50,0:30:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,H-he didn't take the win?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.80,0:30:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In this round,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.80,0:30:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He's aiming for a direct hit on Akagi come hell or high water!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.22,0:30:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.24,0:30:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,[groovy music starts playing]
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.01,0:30:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,9 man.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.52,0:30:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! He's caught him.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.24,0:30:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi's 3, 6, 9 Man tiles...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.52,0:31:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as his 2, 5, and 8 Man tiles have been taken care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.28,0:31:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And what remains in his hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.02,0:31:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are certainly 1, 4, and 7 Man tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.30,0:31:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Our waits are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.96,0:31:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,2 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.68,0:32:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You've drawn it, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.08,0:32:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,4 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.95,0:32:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.95,0:32:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Red Dragon, Ittsuu. 4 Dora.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.30,0:32:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,An 18,000 point win as dealer.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.06,0:32:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but could we have a bit of a break?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.94,0:32:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to let us settle our spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.94,0:32:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well. It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.60,0:32:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Master, shall we--?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.66,0:32:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in a precarious state, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.48,0:33:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.36,0:33:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't beat Ichikawa, can we?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.38,0:33:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.54,0:33:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason why you should lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.52,0:33:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly Ichikawa's play is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.30,0:33:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,His tenacity and intuition are superhuman.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.15,0:33:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,However, by no means...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.15,0:33:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,was Akagi's game worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.60,0:33:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In this last hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.50,0:33:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi consistently dodged Ichikawa's waits.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.40,0:33:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And he finally managed to get into a 1 or 4 Man wait Tenpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.12,0:33:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Nangou, If you had drawn the 7 Man tile what would you have discarded?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.76,0:34:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, considering...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.10,0:34:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Supposing that the 1, 4, and 7 Man tiles are similarly dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.30,0:34:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably the 7 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.46,0:34:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.46,0:34:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a small chance 7 Man would pass,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.04,0:34:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,then I'd preserve my Tenpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.82,0:34:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking that way is merely human nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.86,0:34:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But Akagi didn't try to pursue that small chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.65,0:34:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If he took the small risk that the 7 Man would pass,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.08,0:34:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Ichikawa would have gotten an additional Dora, raising his hand to a Baiman win.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.92,0:34:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And Akagi would have gone bust.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.79,0:34:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,A normal person...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.54,0:34:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,how could they even think that far?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.16,0:34:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if they did consider it,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.86,0:34:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,how could they resist the small chance the 7 Man would pass?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.56,0:34:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't win like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.30,0:35:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A one in ten thousand chance,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.84,0:35:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,an ephemeral "if"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.84,0:35:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Pursuing something so transient, there's no way to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.88,0:35:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Master, just one more hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.76,0:35:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This recess...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.32,0:35:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,was unnecessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.82,0:35:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.82,0:35:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The game flow is now clearly with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.86,0:35:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens if they stop that flow?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.86,0:35:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.92,0:35:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's a trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.86,0:35:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, my man
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.22,0:35:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Will tell us his tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.98,0:36:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.62,0:36:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Nangou.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.27,0:36:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't forgotten, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.76,0:37:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,err...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.62,0:37:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanted to speak to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.58,0:37:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,As this match is more than likely to get complicated,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.36,0:37:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,During the match, you might, just a little,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.78,0:37:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,help us out.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.26,0:37:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"Help us out?"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.54,0:37:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.54,0:37:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,When I speak,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.08,0:37:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell us what Akagi is going for in the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.98,0:37:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I'll cheat for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.28,0:37:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you help us win this match, then you...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.77,0:37:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,will get your 3 Million cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.67,0:37:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Not bad at all, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.50,0:37:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Nangou, you don't smell of roses to begin with do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.05,0:37:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do this, it will decide the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.32,0:37:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If he's waiting on Pin tiles, your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.06,0:37:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If Sou tiles, your nose,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.06,0:38:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If Man tiles, your chin.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.48,0:38:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If Honor tiles, your ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.93,0:38:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If he can't win, then lightly, on your head...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.90,0:38:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I refuse!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.94,0:38:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That guy. He's certainly asking for it, isn't he.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.05,0:38:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.79,0:38:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That kind of guy will wait until the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.58,0:38:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone thinks of themselves first.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.61,0:38:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.08,0:39:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,N-nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.84,0:39:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of Ichikawa's last dealer win,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.14,0:39:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We only have 5,000 points left.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.14,0:39:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If Akagi deals into Ichikawa's hand just one more time,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.88,0:39:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.13,0:39:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we lose...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.13,0:39:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,all that cash...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.52,0:39:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason for us to have to pay that!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.18,0:39:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy fuck what an utterly shit hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.78,0:40:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just no use.\NWe can't possibly win!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.68,0:40:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,With that initial hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.59,0:40:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ichikawa is already two tiles from winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.59,0:40:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and furthermore he's got two Dora tiles!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.20,0:40:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If he has a self-drawn PinFu, Iitsuu win,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.06,0:40:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a possible Haneman win!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.38,0:40:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,1 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.62,0:40:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,7 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.50,0:40:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,8 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.68,0:40:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,7 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.60,0:40:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess there's nothing we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.14,0:41:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Even yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.34,0:41:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,2 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.94,0:41:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I see!\NI see what he's getting at...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.62,0:41:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He's hinting he has a Kokushi Musou or a Chinitsu to tie their hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.34,0:41:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The hell!? Does he have a Kokushi Musou?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.22,0:41:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi with 2 Man discard.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.34,0:41:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,5 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.60,0:41:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right next to a Dora tile!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.38,0:42:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If he's discarding that dangerous tile, then I was right; He's got a Kokushi Musou!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.52,0:42:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,4 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.58,0:42:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Discard that and it's over!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.96,0:42:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this madness?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.62,0:42:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He's aiming for a Kokushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.02,0:42:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Nangou.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.14,0:42:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't look too well, do you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.82,0:42:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Nangou, at this point in the match,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.70,0:42:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what will happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.70,0:42:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Will it end? Or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.21,0:42:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.48,0:42:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You're acting odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.18,0:42:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I-it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.80,0:43:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I said it's nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.44,0:43:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Nangou,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.44,0:43:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like that time once again, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.68,0:43:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.86,0:43:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to discard this 5 Pin
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.84,0:43:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's pretty dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.74,0:43:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But at the same time, the 2 Pin is entirely safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.21,0:43:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.80,0:43:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If I deal into someone's hand it's all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.36,0:43:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd survive if only {\b1\i1}you died.{\b0\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.90,0:43:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.46,0:43:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.16,0:43:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi turned it around for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.14,0:43:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He saved this useless guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.20,0:43:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I not believe in him now!?!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.44,0:43:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm betting... on him!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.95,0:43:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.95,0:44:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Show it to me one more time,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.94,0:44:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely you,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.78,0:44:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,will let loose your superhuman ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.46,0:44:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I... BEILEEEB in you!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.28,0:44:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,?????????????
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.26,0:44:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,2 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.36,0:44:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,West.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.22,0:45:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,North.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.38,0:45:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,8 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.74,0:45:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. This is perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.50,0:45:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If he discards the 5 Man, he's set up for a PinFu, Iitsuu 2 Dora Haneman win!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.18,0:45:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?!?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.06,0:45:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.52,0:45:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,1 Pin. One Dora.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.52,0:45:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a small win.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.52,0:45:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This is crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.52,0:45:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't he deliver the coup-de-grace?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.26,0:45:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.26,0:46:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A judgment typical of a man as pragmatic as Ichikawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.37,0:46:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ichikawa has 100,000 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.98,0:46:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If he deals into anyone's hand it's of no matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.54,0:46:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing Ichikawa wants to prevent is Akagi winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.46,0:46:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That Kokushi Musou,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.46,0:46:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is likely a bluff.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.58,0:46:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but in the small chance it's real, he'd be dealing into Akagi's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.20,0:46:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, before he can draw his winning tile,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.04,0:46:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's better throwing away his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.60,0:46:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what he thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.60,0:46:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you, Ichikawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.02,0:46:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well I'll be. Your plan was more skillful than theirs, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.08,0:46:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Using that shit hand and draws,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.76,0:46:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and in an instant,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.42,0:46:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,forcing Ichikawa out of the Dealer's position.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.40,0:46:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, but it just might change the game flow entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.20,0:46:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Might it not, Akagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.56,0:47:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, thank god!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.30,0:47:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe in Akagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.64,0:47:16.51,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(226.479,154)}East Hand Three (repeated)
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.12,0:47:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two Dora 5 Man tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.74,0:47:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Tiles to discard that might mean death.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.28,0:47:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the Mahjong I've seen Akagi play in a nutshell.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.92,0:47:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To turns lies into truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.48,0:47:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,he will, without hesitation, undergo any hardship, shed his own blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.68,0:47:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and to that end...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.88,0:47:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What a starting starting hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.64,0:47:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a short while ago, he looked like he was going through hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.69,0:48:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.22,0:48:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever he survives a near-death encounter,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.50,0:48:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi returns with a monster hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.10,0:48:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,this above all,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.84,0:48:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is AKAGI'S MAHJONG!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.94,0:49:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.42,0:49:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo, Honitsu, Chanta, SanAnkou, Red Dragon, Green Dragon, one Dora.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.98,0:49:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A San-Baimain win!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.76,0:49:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,???????????????
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.80,0:49:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You've survived, haven't you, Akagi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.67,0:49:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,As you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.14,0:49:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you call upon that demonic luck another time?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.37,0:49:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In this match, that 5 Man tile,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.10,0:49:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and Dora you discarded were reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.95,0:49:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,5 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.82,0:49:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,4 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.74,0:49:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's where you're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.03,0:49:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Before long you'll understand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.47,0:49:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is getting interesting.
